a.xlink:title: The main orchestrator for setting up all grid-related components.
Allocates the memory for the UserMG and UserCtx hierarchy.
Orchestrates the assignment of physical coordinates to all DMDA objects.
Orchestrates the calculation of all grid metrics.
Creates and initializes all PETSc Vec objects for all fields.
Orchestrates the parsing and setting of grid dimensions for all blocks.
Orchestrates the creation of DMDA objects for every block and multigrid level.
Retrieves the current logging level from the environment variable LOG_LEVEL.
Populates coarse grid coordinates by restricting from a fine grid.
A router that populates the coordinates for a single finest-level DMDA.
Programmatically generates and sets grid coordinates based on user parameters.
Reads physical coordinates from a file and populates the DMDA for a specific block.
Computes a stretched coordinate along one dimension.
Ensure a right-handed metric basis (Csi, Eta, Zet) and a positive Jacobian (Aj) over the whole domain...
Calculates the cell-centered inverse Jacobian determinant (1/J), including boundary extrapolation,...
Computes the physical location of cell centers and the spacing between them.
Computes the primary face metric components (Csi, Eta, Zet), including boundary extrapolation,...
Computes metrics centered on constant-i faces (i-faces).
Computes metrics centered on constant-j faces (j-faces).
Computes metrics centered on constant-k faces (k-faces).
Computes the max-min values of the grid metrics.
Computes the divergence of the grid metrics and identifies the maximum value.
Updates the local vector (including ghost points) from its corresponding global vector.
Checks if a given function is in the allow-list.
Determines the grid source and calls the appropriate parsing routine.
